Timestamp Cleanup

docker_data_all <- docker_data_all %>%
  mutate(timestamp = as.numeric(timestamp)*1000)

host_mem_tibble <- host_mem_tibble %>%
  mutate(Timestamp = as.numeric(parse_iso_8601(Timestamp))*1000)

host_cpu0_tibble <- host_cpu0_tibble %>%
  mutate(Timestamp = as.numeric(parse_iso_8601(Timestamp))*1000)
host_cpu1_tibble <- host_cpu1_tibble %>%
  mutate(Timestamp = as.numeric(parse_iso_8601(Timestamp))*1000)

Boxplot

With extreme outliers removed

combined_duration <- tibble(
  Azure = azure_times_tibble$duration,
  Google = google_tibble$duration,
  AWSLocalDB = amazon_localdb_times_tibble$duration,
  AWSLiveDB = amazon_livedb_times_tibble$duration
  )
gathered_combined_duration <- combined_duration %>% 
  gather(Provider, Count)

gathered_combined_duration_without_aws_outlier <- gathered_combined_duration %>%
  filter(Count > 10000, Count < 30000)

gathered_combined_duration_without_aws_outlier %>%
  ggplot( aes(x=Provider, y=Count, fill=Provider)) +
    geom_boxplot() +
    theme_light() +
    theme(legend.position="none") +
    ggtitle("Timing boxplot") +
    xlab("") +
    ylab("Pipeline execution time (in ms)") +
    ggtitle("Boxplot of pipeline execution time for different cloud providers")

Docker Metrics further processing

azure_with_name = azure_times_tibble %>%
  add_column(Provider = "Azure") %>%
  mutate(jobId = row_number())
google_with_name = google_tibble %>%
  add_column(Provider = "Google")%>%
  mutate(jobId = row_number())
amazon_localdb_with_name = amazon_localdb_times_tibble %>%
  add_column(Provider = "AWSLocalDB")%>%
  mutate(jobId = row_number())
amazon_livedb_with_name = amazon_livedb_times_tibble %>%
  add_column(Provider = "AWSLiveDB")%>%
  mutate(jobId = row_number())

time_data_all <- as_tibble(rbind(azure_with_name, google_with_name, amazon_localdb_with_name, amazon_livedb_with_name))
head(time_data_all)
## # A tibble: 6 x 11
##   jobId duration startTime endTime stageCheck.dura~ stageCheck.star~
##   <int>    <int>     <dbl>   <dbl>            <int>            <dbl>
## 1     1    12531   1.60e12 1.60e12              190    1600251914891
## 2     2    11926   1.60e12 1.60e12              201    1600251934667
## 3     3    12859   1.60e12 1.60e12              194    1600251959577
## 4     4    12061   1.60e12 1.60e12              223    1600251979561
## 5     5    11635   1.60e12 1.60e12              203    1600252004622
## 6     6    11285   1.60e12 1.60e12              208    1600252024586
## # ... with 5 more variables: stageSetup.duration <int>,
## #   stageSetup.startTime <dbl>, stageTest.duration <int>,
## #   stageTest.startTime <dbl>, Provider <chr>
jobResourceUsage <- time_data_all %>% 
    mutate(dummy=TRUE) %>%
    left_join(docker_data_all %>% mutate(dummy=TRUE)) %>%
    filter(endTime > docker_data_all$timestamp, docker_data_all$timestamp > startTime) %>%
    select(-dummy)

averageResourceUsageJob <- jobResourceUsage %>%
  select(jobId, Provider, CPUPerc, MemPerc, duration, timestamp, stageTest.duration) %>%
  group_by(jobId, Provider, duration, timestamp, stageTest.duration) %>%
  summarise(CPUPerc = sum(CPUPerc), MemPerc = sum(MemPerc))

maxResourceUsageJob <- averageResourceUsageJob %>%
  select(jobId, Provider, CPUPerc, MemPerc, duration, stageTest.duration) %>%
  group_by(jobId, Provider, duration, stageTest.duration) %>%
  summarise(maxCPU = max(CPUPerc), maxMem = max(MemPerc)) %>%
  gather(Resource, Percentage, -jobId, -Provider, -duration, -stageTest.duration)

Resource usage ec2

resource_provider <- tibble(
  Provider= c("Azure","Google","AWSLocalDB","AWSLiveDB"),
  bench_start = c(1600251914163, 1600256804716,1600254159382,1600261762951),
  bench_stop = c(1600254146173, 1600259773899,1600256792246,1600264292832)
)
resource_provide_cp0 <- resource_provider %>% 
    mutate(dummy=TRUE) %>%
    left_join(host_cpu0_tibble %>% mutate(Observation = row_number()) %>% mutate(dummy=TRUE, CPU="cpu0")) %>%
    filter(bench_stop >= Timestamp, Timestamp >= bench_start) %>%
    select(-dummy)

resource_provider_mem <- resource_provider %>% 
    mutate(dummy=TRUE) %>%
    left_join(host_mem_tibble %>% mutate(Observation = row_number()) %>% mutate(dummy=TRUE, metric="mem")) %>%
    filter(bench_stop >= Timestamp, Timestamp >= bench_start) %>%
    select(-dummy)

resource_provider_cp1 <- resource_provider %>% 
    mutate(dummy=TRUE) %>%
    left_join(host_cpu1_tibble %>% mutate(Observation = row_number()) %>% mutate(dummy=TRUE, CPU="cpu1")) %>%
    filter(bench_stop > Timestamp, Timestamp > bench_start) %>%
    select(-dummy)

resource_cpu_tot <- as_tibble(rbind(resource_provide_cp0,resource_provider_cp1))

resource_provider_mem %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=Observation, y=Maximum, color = Provider)) +
    facet_grid(vars(Provider)) +
    geom_line() +
    theme_light() +
    theme(legend.position="none") +
    ylab("Max MEM usage in %") +
    xlab("CloudWatch Datapoint (5min interval)") +
    ggtitle("Max MEM usage per provider")

Based on max values over 5 min

resource_cpu_tot %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=Observation, y=Average, color = CPU)) +
    facet_grid(vars(Provider)) +
    geom_line() +
    theme_light() +
    ylab("Mean CPU usage in %") +
    xlab("CloudWatch Datapoint (5min interval)") +
    ggtitle("Average CPU usage per provider")
